│ The `ScheduleData` structure is responsible    │
│ for managing scheduling information for        │
│ instructions in the SLP vectorizer. It tracks  │
│ dependencies, scheduling regions, and          │
│ instruction bundles. The `Inst` field points   │
│ to the associated instruction, and the `TE`    │
│ field links the `ScheduleData` to its          │
│ corresponding `TreeEntry`.                     │
│                                                │
│ The SSA dominance issue might occur if the     │
│ scheduling information is not updated          │
│ correctly when instructions are inserted into  │
│ the IR. Specifically, the `FirstInBundle` and  │
│ `NextInBundle` fields must ensure that the     │
│ insertion point respects SSA dominance rules.  │
│                                                │
│ To address this, I will inspect the            │
│ `BlockScheduling` structure, which manages     │
│ scheduling regions and interacts with          │
│ `ScheduleData`. This will help determine how   │
│ insertion points are chosen and whether they   │
│ respect SSA dominance rules. I will now search │
│ for the implementation of the                  │
│ `BlockScheduling` methods.                     │
