│ The `scheduleBlock` method is responsible for  │
│ scheduling instructions in a basic block. It   │
│ ensures that instructions are scheduled in the │
│ correct order, respecting dependencies and     │
│ maintaining SSA dominance rules. The method    │
│ uses a ready-list to manage instructions that  │
│ are ready to be scheduled and moves            │
│ instructions to their appropriate positions in │
│ the IR.                                        │
│                                                │
│ The key part of the method is the loop where   │
│ instructions are moved:                        │
│                                                │
│ ```cpp                                         │
│ for (ScheduleData *BundleMember = Picked;      │
│ BundleMember;                                  │
│      BundleMember =                            │
│ BundleMember->NextInBundle) {                  │
│   Instruction *PickedInst =                    │
│ BundleMember->Inst;                            │
│   if (PickedInst->getNextNonDebugInstruction() │
│ != LastScheduledInst)                          │
│     PickedInst->moveAfter(LastScheduledInst->g │
│ etPrevNode());                                 │
│   LastScheduledInst = PickedInst;              │
│ }                                              │
│ ```                                            │
│                                                │
│ This loop moves instructions to their          │
│ scheduled positions. If the insertion point is │
│ not chosen correctly, it could lead to SSA     │
│ dominance violations. The `moveAfter` method   │
│ ensures that the instruction is moved after    │
│ the specified instruction, but it does not     │
│ automatically verify SSA dominance.            │
│                                                │
│ To address the SSA dominance issue, I will     │
│ ensure that the insertion point is chosen such │
│ that the moved instruction dominates all its   │
│ uses. This can be achieved by verifying the    │
│ dominance relationship before moving the       │
│ instruction.                                   │
│                                                │
│ I will now prepare a patch to modify the       │
│ `scheduleBlock` method to include dominance    │
│ checks before moving instructions.             │
